def extract_entities(sentence):
    # Define regular expression patterns for each entity type
    patterns = {
        'politician': r'\b[A-Z][a-z]+ [A-Z][a-z]+\b',
        'person': r'\b[A-Z][a-z]+ [A-Z][a-z]+\b',  # Same pattern as politician
        'organization': r'\b[A-Z][a-z]+ [A-Z][a-z]+\b',  # Same pattern as politician
        'politicalparty': r'\b[A-Z][a-z]+ Party\b',
        'event': r'\d{4} [A-Za-z ]+ election',
        'election': r'\d{4} [A-Za-z ]+ election',
        'country': r'\b[A-Z][a-z]+ [A-Za-z]+ of [A-Za-z]+\b',
        'location': r'\b[A-Z][a-z]+\b',  # Simple location name
       'misc': r'\b[A-Z][a-z]+\b'  # Miscellaneous entity
    }

    # Initialize output string
    output = ''

    # Iterate over each word in the sentence
    words = sentence.split()
    i = 0
    while i < len(words):
        word = words[i]
        # Check if the word matches any of the entity patterns
        for entity_type, pattern in patterns.items():
            match = re.match(pattern, word)
            if match:
                # If it matches, add the entity tag to the output string
                output += f'<{entity_type}>{word}</{entity_type}>'
                break

    }

    # Replace entity mentions in the original sentence with their tagged versions
    for entity_type, entity_values in entities
